Happiness is even harder to define.

475
00:22:03,856 --> 00:22:06,958
Well, it's been a long time since
I've gone drinking.

476
00:22:06,959 --> 00:22:08,193
Goodnight.

477
00:22:08,194 --> 00:22:09,334
Goodnight.

478
00:22:22,908 --> 00:22:24,943
Did you want something, Rei?

479
00:22:24,944 --> 00:22:26,578
I got lost.

480
00:22:26,579 --> 00:22:29,889
Oh, really? Then you want to
leave here with me?

481
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:32,550
That's okay.

482
00:22:32,551 --> 00:22:34,919
But you won't be able to get home
by yourself, right?

483
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:37,030
That's none of your business, you old hag.

484
00:22:38,757 --> 00:22:39,757
What?

485
00:22:39,758 --> 00:22:42,248
I can go home by myself,
so leave me alone, you old hag.

486
00:22:43,329 --> 00:22:46,364
It's not nice to call someone an old hag.

487
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:48,566
But you are an old hag, aren't you?

488
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:52,237
I'm going to get mad. You need
a good scolding from Director lkari.

489
00:22:52,238 --> 00:22:55,073
That's what the Director calls you.

490
00:22:55,074 --> 00:22:55,907
That...

491
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:57,508
He says, “That old hag is pushy,”

492
00:22:57,509 --> 00:22:59,619
or that he, “doesn't need that old hag anymore.”

493
00:23:00,312 --> 00:23:01,713
He says, “That old hag is pushy,”

